WEBVTT

00:09.009 --> 00:11.849
[hissing]

00:27.068 --> 00:28.238
<i>I...</i>

00:28.695 --> 00:31.605
<i>am the jungle's eyes.</i>

00:32.573 --> 00:34.834
<i>I can see the past...</i>

00:35.243 --> 00:37.083
<i>and the future.</i>

00:37.328 --> 00:39.038
[hissing]

00:39.289 --> 00:41.789
<i>It is I, Kaa,</i>

00:42.125 --> 00:45.495
<i>who witnessed the coming of man...</i>

00:45.962 --> 00:47.842
[thunder rumbling]

00:48.006 --> 00:50.546
[Kaa] <i> ...and the jungle...</i>

00:50.633 --> 00:53.473
<i>trying to survive.</i>

00:53.553 --> 00:54.683
[elephant trumpets]

00:54.846 --> 00:56.846
[birds chirping]

00:57.640 --> 00:58.890
[tiger roaring]

00:58.975 --> 01:00.975
[frogs ribbiting]

01:01.061 --> 01:02.811
- [bell ringing]
- [Kaa] <i> I saw chaos</i>

01:02.979 --> 01:06.779
<i>and darkness come to our lands.</i>

01:06.858 --> 01:08.648
[loud roaring]

01:08.818 --> 01:10.818
[people yelling] -[woman gasps]
- [baby cries]

01:18.119 --> 01:19.159
- [material rips]
- Ah!

01:22.874 --> 01:24.134
[roaring]

01:24.417 --> 01:25.587
[woman screams]

01:26.503 --> 01:27.803
[tiger roars]

01:30.256 --> 01:31.926
[man yells]

01:34.010 --> 01:36.850
[Kaa] <i> I saw the tiger, Shere Khan,</i>

01:36.930 --> 01:38.680
<i>killing man,</i>

01:39.933 --> 01:44.403
<i>and breaking the jungle's ancient law.</i>

01:46.397 --> 01:47.977
- [growling]
- [baby crying]

01:48.066 --> 01:49.936
[sniffs]

01:58.076 --> 02:00.076
[hissing] [mouse squeals]

02:07.127 --> 02:08.287
[Kaa] <i> And then,</i>

02:08.877 --> 02:10.708
<i>one fateful night,</i>

02:11.297 --> 02:14.627
<i>I saw the jungle place its hopes</i>

02:14.717 --> 02:16.087
<i>into the hands...</i>

02:16.678 --> 02:19.218
<i>of a small creature,</i>

02:19.806 --> 02:21.636
<i>the like of which...</i>

02:22.142 --> 02:25.232
<i>it had never seen before.</i>

02:25.311 --> 02:27.021
[soft snarl]

02:29.691 --> 02:31.691
[sniffs] [continues sniffing]

02:48.168 --> 02:50.168
[baby babbling]

02:52.213 --> 02:53.763
- [distant roaring]
- Hmm?

03:05.935 --> 03:07.935
[hissing]

03:20.200 --> 03:24.410
- [baby giggling]
- [birds tweeting]

03:40.553 --> 03:41.603
[baby cooing]

03:51.856 --> 03:54.146
[cub whining]

03:55.276 --> 03:57.276
[panting] [whines]

04:09.123 --> 04:10.963
[cubs growling]

04:11.376 --> 04:12.706
- [cub sniffs]
- [baby gasps]

04:14.295 --> 04:15.165
[cubs whining]

04:15.255 --> 04:17.255
[growling]

04:21.010 --> 04:22.140
[snarls]

04:23.304 --> 04:25.314
[baby cooing]

04:26.599 --> 04:27.979
[howls softly]

04:35.483 --> 04:36.903
How did it get here?

04:37.652 --> 04:38.702
I don't know.

04:40.989 --> 04:41.989
Is it hurt?

04:49.289 --> 04:50.289
There's no wound.

04:52.208 --> 04:53.248
It's on its own.

04:54.002 --> 04:56.212
[Vihaan] I've never seen a man-cub before.

04:56.296 --> 04:57.296
It's so...

04:58.923 --> 04:59.973
small.

05:00.800 --> 05:02.470
It doesn't fear us.

05:02.969 --> 05:04.099
[baby babbling]

05:05.346 --> 05:07.096
What are we going to do with it?

05:08.474 --> 05:10.114
- [approaching footsteps]
- [wolves growl]

05:11.311 --> 05:12.691
- Evening, Nisha.
- [flies buzzing]

05:12.812 --> 05:13.692
Vihaan.

05:13.771 --> 05:14.771
[growls]

05:14.856 --> 05:18.186
- It's a lovely night, isn't it?
- What is it that you want, Tabaqui?

05:18.276 --> 05:20.356
[sniffing] What's that I smell?
Fresh kill?

05:20.445 --> 05:22.315
If it's bones you're after,
look elsewhere.

05:23.156 --> 05:24.986
We have enough mouths to feed.

05:25.074 --> 05:27.084
[cubs bark and whine]

05:27.327 --> 05:30.157
I meant no harm, Nisha. [laughs]

05:30.747 --> 05:31.827
[baby coos]

05:32.248 --> 05:33.248
[gasps]

05:35.084 --> 05:36.384
Oh!

05:37.086 --> 05:38.626
[distant roar]

05:39.088 --> 05:40.338
Your master calls.

05:40.840 --> 05:42.050
You best go quickly.

05:43.009 --> 05:44.839
He sounds an ill temper tonight.

05:44.927 --> 05:46.597
That he does. That he does.

05:48.890 --> 05:50.480
And with good reason.

05:51.434 --> 05:52.834
- [Tabaqui screams]
- [wolves growl]

05:53.436 --> 05:56.396
[Tabaqui] I found the man-cub! [laughs]
I found the man-cub!

05:56.481 --> 05:57.771
Finish cleaning him off.

05:57.857 --> 05:59.107
- Nisha.
- Clean him!

05:59.400 --> 06:00.990
- Where you going?
- To Akela.

06:01.903 --> 06:04.113
A council must be held
if we are to keep him.

06:04.197 --> 06:06.677
- [Vihaan] Keep him?
- [Nisha] Don't let him out of your sight.

06:06.741 --> 06:09.121
[Vihaan] We can't keep him!

06:09.577 --> 06:12.707
- [bell ringing]
- [wolves howling]

06:19.295 --> 06:23.255
Nisha, you have called council.
What's the matter at hand?

06:24.133 --> 06:25.303
We've found... a man-cub.

06:28.721 --> 06:30.721
[wolves chattering]

06:33.351 --> 06:37.231
- [male 1] That's not a wolf.
- [female] That doesn't belong here. [male 2] A man-cub! Outrageous.

06:39.107 --> 06:40.017
Well,

06:40.108 --> 06:41.728
this is most unusual indeed.

06:42.902 --> 06:43.902
Nisha,

06:44.070 --> 06:46.490
you wish to raise this cub
as if he were your own?

06:47.281 --> 06:48.531
- I do.
- [wolves whine]

06:49.158 --> 06:50.158
And Vihaan? You, too?

06:53.204 --> 06:54.044
I do.

06:54.122 --> 06:55.292
[male] It's a man-cub!

06:55.540 --> 06:56.540
You know the law.

06:58.459 --> 07:00.169
This cub was not born among us.

07:01.587 --> 07:04.297
So, who,<i> here,</i> speaks for the cub?

07:05.675 --> 07:07.465
[Bagheera pants] I speak for the cub.

07:09.387 --> 07:12.347
The law states that the life of a cub...

07:12.849 --> 07:14.019
may be bought...

07:14.475 --> 07:15.475
for a price.

07:17.103 --> 07:18.193
I brought my payment.

07:18.771 --> 07:19.771
We have one.

07:20.356 --> 07:21.186
[barking]

07:21.274 --> 07:23.114
Who else will speak for the cub?

07:24.277 --> 07:25.277
Baloo does.

07:25.528 --> 07:26.818
[male wolf] Baloo?

07:27.196 --> 07:30.026
- Bagheera...
- He's not a wolf. He has no say.

07:30.116 --> 07:32.756
He's the teacher of your cubs.
That makes him a member of the pack.

07:33.661 --> 07:36.541
I ain't speakin' for no... [snickers]

07:36.873 --> 07:37.963
...a man-cub.

07:38.916 --> 07:42.586
Bagheera, have you lost your mind?
A man-cub living in the jungle?

07:48.926 --> 07:50.926
[sniffs]

07:58.603 --> 07:59.603
[Nisha] Akela,

07:59.687 --> 08:01.437
his parents will come.

08:01.522 --> 08:02.822
[loud roaring]

08:03.024 --> 08:07.284
[Shere Khan] His parents are dead.

08:08.196 --> 08:10.026
I killed them.

08:10.114 --> 08:11.414
[Tabaqui laughs]

08:11.532 --> 08:15.412
There is no one to come looking for him.

08:15.828 --> 08:17.408
[wolves growl]

08:17.538 --> 08:19.748
This is not your concern, Shere Khan.

08:19.832 --> 08:21.382
The cub is mine.

08:21.459 --> 08:24.209
I already tasted its mother's blood.

08:25.505 --> 08:27.795
It is my right.

08:27.882 --> 08:29.972
Your right according to who's law?

08:30.051 --> 08:31.261
Best you leave now.

08:31.344 --> 08:34.974
Careful, Akela.

08:35.431 --> 08:38.181
You do not want to challenge me.

08:38.267 --> 08:39.937
[Tabaqui laughs]

08:40.061 --> 08:41.061
This cub...

08:42.104 --> 08:44.234
is under the protection of the pack.

08:44.607 --> 08:47.187
Should you decide to take me,

08:47.818 --> 08:50.068
you take on the pack.

08:51.239 --> 08:52.239
All of us.

08:52.323 --> 08:55.033
[wolves snarl and bark]

08:56.410 --> 08:57.580
As long as I am leader,

08:58.287 --> 09:00.917
this part of the jungle is closed to you.

09:00.998 --> 09:03.998
- [snarling and barking]
- [Baloo and Bagheera roar]

09:04.335 --> 09:07.955
You cannot be leader forever.

09:08.548 --> 09:10.718
The day you miss your kill,

09:11.634 --> 09:14.514
the man-cub's blood...

09:14.845 --> 09:18.805
will run down my chin.

09:19.225 --> 09:21.225
[wolves growl]

09:30.653 --> 09:32.363
[Akela] The cub is spoken for.

09:32.738 --> 09:34.068
He is one of us.

09:34.574 --> 09:36.664
You will teach him as you would your own.

09:37.577 --> 09:38.907
As long as I am alive,

09:39.662 --> 09:41.712
the pack will stand by the man-cub.

09:42.164 --> 09:43.164
[Akela howls]

09:43.207 --> 09:45.917
[all howl]

09:48.254 --> 09:50.264
[kite screams] [cows mooing]

10:11.569 --> 10:13.569
[bells jingle]
[indistinct human chattering]

10:26.917 --> 10:28.917
[Mowgli laughing]

10:29.003 --> 10:30.003
Whoa!

10:31.964 --> 10:33.974
[leaves rustle]

10:34.717 --> 10:38.047
[Mowgli whooping and laughing]

10:51.442 --> 10:54.862
[Bagheera]
Hunting is sacred, little brother.

10:55.780 --> 10:57.740
It is our right.

10:59.408 --> 11:02.908
But we never do it for sport.

11:03.788 --> 11:06.498
Shh...

11:09.877 --> 11:11.587
[snarling]

11:19.970 --> 11:22.430
[panting] Wait. Wait.

11:24.600 --> 11:26.440
We look them in the eye...

11:27.603 --> 11:28.943
so that the soul...

11:29.355 --> 11:31.265
doesn't depart, alone.

11:34.568 --> 11:36.568
[birds chittering]

12:07.810 --> 12:08.980
[softly] Bagheera...

12:09.937 --> 12:12.257
- [Bagheera grunts softly]
- [crunching insect] [birds caw]

12:19.864 --> 12:21.744
How old is the jungle, Bagheera?

12:22.491 --> 12:25.411
The jungle has been here
since before you were born

12:25.494 --> 12:27.294
and it will be here...

12:29.206 --> 12:30.366
[yawning]

12:30.499 --> 12:31.999
...after you die.

12:32.251 --> 12:34.841
The jungle is eternal.

12:35.629 --> 12:36.799
[Mowgli] Bagheera...

12:38.507 --> 12:42.427
why am I different to the other wolves?

12:50.478 --> 12:51.768
You are no different,

12:52.605 --> 12:53.645
little brother.

12:55.316 --> 12:57.436
You are special.

12:58.402 --> 13:00.862
[Baloo] <i>Of course you're different.</i>
[sniffs]

13:01.280 --> 13:03.280
That's why you need special training.

13:04.033 --> 13:05.623
You know what your trouble is?

13:06.452 --> 13:07.452
Lack of focus.

13:08.120 --> 13:09.120
[Mowgli] Baloo,

13:09.413 --> 13:11.463
how many ants can you fit in your mouth?

13:11.957 --> 13:13.377
Ants are really small

13:13.834 --> 13:15.844
and your mouth is really big.

13:16.504 --> 13:19.424
- I bet...
- Mowgli, will you concentrate?

13:24.595 --> 13:26.255
[scorpion hissing and snapping]

13:26.430 --> 13:27.430
Do... not...

13:30.476 --> 13:31.476
move.

13:37.483 --> 13:38.863
Why do I have to do this?

13:38.943 --> 13:39.943
'Cause I said so.

13:39.985 --> 13:41.695
Tell me the three laws, now.

13:41.779 --> 13:43.569
"No wolf shall have contact with man."

13:43.656 --> 13:45.116
- Next.
- Baloo...

13:46.158 --> 13:48.328
- what happened to your tail?
- Next!

13:48.577 --> 13:50.657
"No wolf shall hunt man's animals.

13:51.288 --> 13:53.998
Above all, the cow, which is sacred!"

13:54.416 --> 13:57.546
Did it fall off?
Is that why you don't have one?

13:57.628 --> 13:59.548
What? Why haven't you got a tail?

13:59.630 --> 14:02.260
I don't know.
I never really thought about it.

14:02.341 --> 14:03.511
Third law.

14:03.801 --> 14:04.641
Now!

14:04.718 --> 14:08.258
"No wolf shall kill man in the jungle,
for killing man only brings danger."

14:08.347 --> 14:10.347
Oh, well. Least you know your laws.

14:10.432 --> 14:13.522
Now, we just got to get you
to run as fast as the other wolves.

14:15.104 --> 14:18.364
- [Baloo chuckles] Oy!
- [Mowgli grunts and groans]

14:18.566 --> 14:21.486
Don't let your guard down. [laughs]

14:22.111 --> 14:24.201
All right,
that's enough for today, Mowgli.

14:24.280 --> 14:25.320
[Mowgli howling]

14:25.406 --> 14:29.196
Straight back to the caves.
No wandering. Run like a wolf, d'you hear?

14:29.660 --> 14:32.120
[Mowgli] I can't hear you!

14:32.204 --> 14:35.124
[Baloo chuckles and sighs]

14:46.552 --> 14:48.552
[sniffs] [birds tweeting]

14:59.315 --> 15:02.065
[cows mooing]

15:02.359 --> 15:04.359
[bells jingling] [indistinct chattering]

15:11.952 --> 15:13.002
[Bhoot] Mowgli!

15:13.829 --> 15:14.909
Hey, Mowgli. [pants]

15:15.706 --> 15:17.626
- Bhoot!
- What are you doing?

15:17.833 --> 15:20.093
- Nothing.
- Hey, do you want to play?

15:21.629 --> 15:23.709
- [Mowgli] Got ya!
- [Bhoot screams] - [laughs] - Oh!

15:26.133 --> 15:28.053
Oh, I nearly had you.

15:29.845 --> 15:30.965
You're good at hiding.

15:31.055 --> 15:34.765
Mum taught me how to hide.
She shows me loads of tricks.

15:34.850 --> 15:37.770
[laughs] So I can protect myself.

15:37.853 --> 15:40.523
She says, "Others can mistake...

15:40.731 --> 15:42.821
individuality for weakness."

15:43.192 --> 15:45.492
That's why they have a go at me sometimes.

15:47.112 --> 15:48.112
Yeah.

15:48.697 --> 15:49.697
Me, too.

15:50.032 --> 15:51.992
Come on. I'll race you home.

15:53.410 --> 15:55.120
- [Bhoot chuckles]
- On my call...

15:56.163 --> 15:57.163
Go!

15:59.166 --> 16:00.876
[Mowgli howls]

16:01.043 --> 16:03.383
[both laughing]

16:07.841 --> 16:09.841
[howling]

16:11.303 --> 16:12.303
Hey.

16:13.681 --> 16:14.681
Hey, brother.

16:15.891 --> 16:17.641
What did Baloo make you do today?

16:17.726 --> 16:19.806
Put a scorpion on me
and told me not to move.

16:19.895 --> 16:21.935
- [laughs]
- [Mowgli] He says I lack focus.

16:22.022 --> 16:24.152
[brother]
Aw, Baloo says that to all of us.

16:25.067 --> 16:26.817
- How was your lesson?
- Fine.

16:26.986 --> 16:28.706
Your brother tells me
you're getting faster.

16:28.779 --> 16:30.699
He can nearly keep pace with me.

16:30.781 --> 16:32.241
He can almost beat Bhoot. [laughs]

16:32.324 --> 16:35.204
Yeah, he should just race
with his freak friend!

16:35.285 --> 16:37.745
It's only natural they spend
so much time with each other.

16:37.830 --> 16:39.370
Freaks have to stick together.

16:39.456 --> 16:41.456
- [wolves growl]
- [Bhoot gasps and grunts]

16:43.002 --> 16:44.002
[Nisha] That's enough.

16:44.795 --> 16:45.795
Ow. That really hurt.

16:45.879 --> 16:46.799
Inside, now.

16:46.880 --> 16:47.880
[wolves whine]

16:47.965 --> 16:48.965
Thanks.

16:49.341 --> 16:51.641
You shouldn't let them pick on you
like that.

16:52.386 --> 16:53.796
We were only playing.

16:54.013 --> 16:55.143
Better go home, Bhoot.

16:55.806 --> 16:57.176
Bye, Mowgli! [chuckles] Ow.

16:57.266 --> 17:00.016
I meant what I said to Mum.
You are getting faster.

17:00.102 --> 17:01.902
Your father was never
much of a runner either.

17:02.229 --> 17:04.769
It's true. I was the slowest in my group.

17:04.857 --> 17:07.896
I never thought I was gonna complete
The Running. I was sure I would fail.

17:08.609 --> 17:11.609
- You're going to be late.
- Have a good hunt, Father.

17:11.696 --> 17:15.027
Before you know it, you'll be coming along
with me. All of you!

17:16.868 --> 17:19.659
- [male wolf] Good hunting!
- [Vihaan] Good hunting all!

17:19.747 --> 17:21.747
[howling]

17:30.090 --> 17:31.590
[Baloo] This is the jungle!

17:32.801 --> 17:35.261
In the jungle, we all hunt.

17:35.345 --> 17:36.675
And... [snarls]

17:36.764 --> 17:39.394
...we are all hunted.

17:39.683 --> 17:41.023
You see what that means.

17:41.810 --> 17:43.230
It means that you...

17:43.771 --> 17:45.311
you don't want to get caught.

17:45.397 --> 17:47.397
[wolves growl and bark]

17:47.733 --> 17:50.693
That's why you can't join the pack...

17:51.278 --> 17:54.528
until you have passed The Running...
[shouts] Pay attention!

17:54.615 --> 17:56.615
[whines]

18:01.163 --> 18:02.623
"What's The Running, Baloo?"

18:03.874 --> 18:06.924
The running is the hunt where you...

18:07.628 --> 18:09.208
are the prey.

18:09.421 --> 18:11.421
[wolves and Mowgli whine]

18:11.924 --> 18:13.054
Now, Bagheera here...

18:13.133 --> 18:14.933
You all know Bagheera, don't you?

18:15.010 --> 18:16.720
Yeah, Bagheera, friendly Bagheera.

18:17.179 --> 18:20.429
In The Running, Bagheera will hunt you,

18:20.516 --> 18:21.926
and if he catches you...

18:22.643 --> 18:23.733
you fail.

18:24.603 --> 18:27.003
What happens if you fail?
[yelling] You don't join the pack!

18:28.690 --> 18:30.690
- [wolves whine]
- [Mowgli whimpers]

18:33.987 --> 18:36.367
But I've never had one of my cubs fail.

18:36.698 --> 18:37.698
[sniffs]

18:39.034 --> 18:42.204
And I'm not gonna start now. [laughs]

18:43.163 --> 18:44.923
[Mowgli gasps]

18:44.998 --> 18:45.998
Good.

18:46.458 --> 18:47.708
Let's practice, shall we?

18:52.673 --> 18:53.673
[Baloo] On my call.

18:54.383 --> 18:57.473
Wait... wait...

18:59.263 --> 19:00.263
Go!

19:01.557 --> 19:02.807
[Baloo] Come on, now!

19:04.893 --> 19:06.023
Pick up the pace!

19:09.857 --> 19:11.277
Come on!

19:13.485 --> 19:14.485
Faster!

19:15.487 --> 19:17.487
[Mowgli panting]

19:24.913 --> 19:27.333
[Baloo breathing heavily]

19:36.758 --> 19:38.758
[monkey chittering]

19:48.645 --> 19:51.435
[monkey chatters]

20:12.711 --> 20:13.711
[grunts]

20:13.754 --> 20:15.714
You were with the monkey-people...

20:16.089 --> 20:19.009
again. [breathes heavily]

20:19.218 --> 20:20.218
[laughs]

20:20.302 --> 20:22.552
[Baloo] The monkey-people have no law,

20:23.347 --> 20:24.597
they're unpredictable,

20:24.681 --> 20:26.481
and they can't even speak proper.

20:26.892 --> 20:30.562
- [Mowgli] I think they're funny.
- [Baloo] There's nothing funny about them.

20:30.646 --> 20:32.306
You keep away, do you understand?

20:32.397 --> 20:36.187
- I'm not afraid of them.
- Only fools feel no fear, Mowgli.

20:36.610 --> 20:39.030
[Baloo]
The monkey-people are especially foolish.

20:39.279 --> 20:40.989
There's nothing they're afraid of.

20:41.615 --> 20:44.275
Well, except Kaa. [laughs]

20:44.618 --> 20:46.698
Oh, they can't even lay eyes on her.

20:46.787 --> 20:47.787
[Mowgli] Who's Kaa?

20:47.871 --> 20:50.871
- Oh, you don't want to meet Kaa.
- [Mowgli chuckles]

20:51.083 --> 20:53.133
Kaa the Python...

20:53.210 --> 20:55.250
is as old as the jungle.

20:56.797 --> 20:58.757
She sees the past...

20:59.424 --> 21:00.764
and the future.

21:00.842 --> 21:02.842
[flies buzzing]

21:03.303 --> 21:05.853
- [Mowgli pants]
- [shouts] Turn around!

21:09.977 --> 21:10.977
Eyes forward.

21:11.019 --> 21:13.019
[flies buzzing]

21:17.776 --> 21:18.776
The cow...

21:18.944 --> 21:21.284
had been killed
and left there to be found.

21:21.738 --> 21:27.578
- [male 1] The tiger! He's come back!
- Only Khan would kill man's cattle.

21:27.661 --> 21:30.501
- [male 2] One man-cub will bring more men!
- It's Shere Khan!

21:30.580 --> 21:32.920
Akela, we knew this would happen!
We told you!

21:33.000 --> 21:36.340
Can't you see, Akela,
the man-cub is putting us all in danger.

21:36.420 --> 21:40.590
- You were wrong to ever take him in!
- We should give him to the tiger!

21:40.674 --> 21:42.594
- Akela, no!
- [male wolf] Save the pack!

21:43.051 --> 21:44.051
Please.

21:45.804 --> 21:47.064
He is one of us.

21:50.309 --> 21:51.769
I will see to this matter.

21:52.561 --> 21:53.561
Go!

21:54.187 --> 21:56.187
[howling]

22:05.073 --> 22:07.583
Shere Khan wants to bring war
to the jungle.

22:08.702 --> 22:09.702
War?

22:10.662 --> 22:12.962
With man? Is he out of his mind?

22:13.040 --> 22:14.040
War with me.

22:15.959 --> 22:17.289
He knows I'm getting old.

22:17.919 --> 22:20.339
This is his way of bringing chaos
to the pack.

22:21.214 --> 22:24.014
- Khan wants the boy.
- We can protect him.

22:24.092 --> 22:26.972
You know there is only one way
to protect him.

22:27.512 --> 22:29.432
He must go to the man village.

22:30.057 --> 22:31.477
You're forgetting, Bagheera,

22:32.017 --> 22:34.727
this was always more
than just a good deed.

22:35.479 --> 22:36.939
The jungle is changing.

22:38.023 --> 22:41.443
Man is taking more of it,
as each season passes.

22:42.736 --> 22:43.736
And the boy...

22:44.446 --> 22:47.696
may just be our only hope of survival.

22:48.492 --> 22:50.872
The jungle is no longer safe for him.

22:51.828 --> 22:55.168
- The pack won't accept him.
- They will if he passes The Running.

22:55.874 --> 22:57.134
Baloo, is he ready?

22:57.209 --> 22:59.629
Of course he's not ready.
He's not a wolf.

22:59.711 --> 23:01.001
Then make him ready.

23:02.923 --> 23:04.933
[Baloo sighs]

23:06.968 --> 23:08.008
[Baloo] Right,

23:08.095 --> 23:09.385
no more messing about.

23:10.305 --> 23:11.965
Can you run as fast as a wolf?

23:12.641 --> 23:13.731
No, you can't.

23:14.518 --> 23:17.518
You've got hands with fingers on the ends,

23:17.604 --> 23:18.614
so let's use them.

23:18.688 --> 23:19.688
What?

23:20.315 --> 23:22.395
Now jump, to there.

23:23.318 --> 23:24.438
Come on, hurry up.

23:24.569 --> 23:26.239
[Mowgli pants]

23:27.656 --> 23:29.406
[grunts, thuds]

23:29.950 --> 23:30.950
[Baloo laughs]

23:31.034 --> 23:32.454
[birds fluttering and chirping]

23:32.536 --> 23:33.536
Again.

23:33.662 --> 23:35.372
[grunts, thuds]

23:35.580 --> 23:36.920
[Baloo] Oh, nearly!

23:41.044 --> 23:42.044
[grunting]

23:42.921 --> 23:45.421
Ah! [yelling]

23:45.507 --> 23:46.797
- Yes!
- Baloo!

23:46.883 --> 23:48.893
[laughing]

23:49.886 --> 23:51.006
[Mowgli grunts, thuds]

23:52.097 --> 23:53.097
[groans]

23:55.851 --> 23:57.601
[birds cawing]

24:14.077 --> 24:16.077
[growl echoing through water]

24:41.938 --> 24:43.268
[bubbling]

24:47.569 --> 24:49.569
[Shere Khan sighs]

24:53.325 --> 24:55.485
[moaning]

24:58.371 --> 25:00.871
[Shere Khan growls]

25:12.093 --> 25:13.473
[shouts] Ah!

25:17.015 --> 25:18.725
[roaring]

25:23.897 --> 25:25.517
[panting]

25:26.399 --> 25:27.399
Ah!

25:28.193 --> 25:30.453
[grunting]

25:32.239 --> 25:33.739
[yells]

25:34.199 --> 25:36.409
[birds calling and fluttering]

25:36.493 --> 25:38.503
[growls]

25:38.954 --> 25:40.254
[gasps]

25:43.833 --> 25:46.553
[distant roaring]

25:53.009 --> 25:55.259
[approaching footsteps]

25:56.263 --> 25:58.273
[growling]

26:09.317 --> 26:11.397
[loud pounding]

26:14.781 --> 26:17.031
[Mowgli breathing heavily]

26:48.273 --> 26:50.283
[soft trumpeting]

26:56.114 --> 26:58.034
[Bagheera snarls]

26:58.116 --> 26:59.116
What happened?

27:02.537 --> 27:05.167
[Bagheera panting]

27:10.295 --> 27:12.295
[trumpeting] [birds tweeting]

27:24.768 --> 27:26.098
Come on, little brother.

27:26.645 --> 27:27.645
Time to go home.

27:33.276 --> 27:35.276
[growls softly] [indistinct human chatter]

27:51.086 --> 27:53.126
[Bagheera]
Do you know why those men have come?

27:53.213 --> 27:55.223
[bells dinging]

27:56.424 --> 27:59.764
[Bagheera] They've come to hunt the tiger
that steals their cattle.

28:00.136 --> 28:01.216
Will they kill him?

28:01.304 --> 28:02.304
It won't be easy.

28:03.682 --> 28:05.022
Shere Khan...

28:05.517 --> 28:06.517
is clever.

28:08.061 --> 28:09.191
Very dangerous.

28:12.774 --> 28:13.774
Mowgli...

28:15.318 --> 28:17.198
the jungle is no longer safe for you.

28:19.114 --> 28:23.084
But if you were to be in a place
where Shere Khan would never go,

28:23.827 --> 28:25.197
then you would be safe.

28:26.329 --> 28:27.959
Where does Shere Khan never go?

28:29.124 --> 28:30.254
Mmm...

28:30.417 --> 28:32.667
you know... the man village.

28:33.169 --> 28:34.499
Why would I go there?

28:39.676 --> 28:41.586
Because you are a man-cub.

28:44.764 --> 28:47.024
I have seen the way
you look at the village.

28:47.308 --> 28:48.688
[Mowgli whimpers]

28:48.810 --> 28:50.560
You are one of them.

28:52.021 --> 28:53.111
I'm a wolf.

28:53.189 --> 28:54.229
Mowgli...

28:54.649 --> 28:56.739
[Bagheera sighs]

28:59.404 --> 29:01.744
He wants your blood, little brother.

29:01.990 --> 29:04.910
It was Shere Khan
who killed your man-parents

29:04.993 --> 29:06.663
all those seasons ago,

29:07.287 --> 29:09.707
and now he wants to kill you.

29:11.416 --> 29:12.666
The pack will protect me.

29:12.751 --> 29:14.291
If you fail The Running...

29:14.377 --> 29:15.247
I won't fail.

29:15.336 --> 29:16.336
You won't...

29:17.213 --> 29:18.673
be able to join the pack.

29:19.048 --> 29:20.628
[shouts] I won't fail!

29:22.385 --> 29:23.755
Then promise me this.

29:25.472 --> 29:26.722
If you do fail...

29:28.016 --> 29:29.426
you will go to the village.

29:30.935 --> 29:32.185
Promise me, Mowgli.

29:43.907 --> 29:45.907
[Mowgli pants] [indistinct human chatter]

29:57.545 --> 29:59.755
- [woman groans]
- [man] Good evening!

29:59.923 --> 30:01.933
[laughter] [men speaking Hindi]

30:16.689 --> 30:18.689
[fire crackling]

30:23.029 --> 30:25.409
[Lockwood] Don't worry.
I'll kill your tiger.

30:25.573 --> 30:27.123
How many's he taken this time?

30:28.201 --> 30:29.201
Careful!

30:29.536 --> 30:30.746
Quickly, now. Come on.

30:30.954 --> 30:34.464
- [Tabaqui pants]
- [flies buzzing]

30:40.129 --> 30:41.589
[Tabaqui laughs]

30:45.802 --> 30:47.182
[whining]

30:47.554 --> 30:51.064
[exclaiming]

30:58.231 --> 30:59.151
[sizzling]

30:59.232 --> 31:00.482
[sighs]

31:08.783 --> 31:10.333
[snarls]

31:10.702 --> 31:12.872
Did you smell the blood, man-cub?

31:14.163 --> 31:15.293
[whispers] What is it?

31:19.168 --> 31:23.088
- The creature that did that to your tail.
- [Tabaqui] It's called "fire."

31:24.007 --> 31:25.627
It's hotter than the sun.

31:26.968 --> 31:28.758
And it's quicker than the panther.

31:30.722 --> 31:33.222
Your kind use dark magic, man-cub.

31:33.308 --> 31:34.848
They're not my kind.

31:34.934 --> 31:36.944
[laughs]

31:41.524 --> 31:42.524
Sometimes...

31:43.484 --> 31:46.284
I dream I'm a tiger. [growls]

31:47.113 --> 31:49.163
But I always wake up a hyena.

31:52.911 --> 31:53.911
[laughs]

31:53.953 --> 31:56.583
[groans] Ow.

31:58.917 --> 31:59.917
Ooh.

32:00.418 --> 32:02.418
[birds tweeting] [elephant trumpets]

32:12.388 --> 32:14.388
You should try and get some sleep.

32:19.729 --> 32:21.649
You'll want to be rested for tomorrow.

32:31.491 --> 32:32.991
What's bothering you, my love?

32:34.827 --> 32:36.537
All I've ever wanted...

32:38.957 --> 32:40.377
my whole life...

32:42.377 --> 32:43.707
is to be a wolf.

32:47.882 --> 32:50.182
For the others to see me as an...

32:52.345 --> 32:53.345
equal.

32:56.474 --> 32:58.944
This is my chance to prove myself.

33:00.269 --> 33:02.109
To prove that I'm one of them.

33:04.023 --> 33:05.403
To prove that I belong.

33:05.483 --> 33:06.483
You belong.

33:10.363 --> 33:11.863
You belong, Mowgli.

33:14.492 --> 33:17.792
Don't, ever, let anyone
make you think otherwise.

33:21.207 --> 33:23.667
You will always be my son, Mowgli.

33:26.212 --> 33:28.132
Nothing can ever change that.

33:59.203 --> 34:01.083
[Akela] You are about to take part

34:01.289 --> 34:03.249
in one of our oldest traditions.

34:04.792 --> 34:06.502
The Running of the Pack.

34:07.628 --> 34:09.458
Those of you who pass the test...

34:10.965 --> 34:12.335
will have earned the right...

34:13.301 --> 34:14.301
to join us...

34:14.844 --> 34:15.934
in the night hunt.

34:19.306 --> 34:20.677
As is customary...

34:22.060 --> 34:24.600
Bagheera will perform his task as chaser.

34:24.687 --> 34:26.687
[heart beating]

34:27.940 --> 34:29.030
Mowgli!

34:29.609 --> 34:30.989
Good luck, Mowgli!

34:34.112 --> 34:36.123
[wolves growl and whine]

34:41.204 --> 34:42.333
Face the hill.

34:48.710 --> 34:49.801
Good luck, brother.

34:49.879 --> 34:54.179
[Akela] I must warn you.
Bagheera has been told not to hold back.

34:54.257 --> 34:56.257
[growls]

34:57.595 --> 34:59.215
[panting]

34:59.972 --> 35:00.972
[Akela] On my call.

35:06.938 --> 35:07.978
Go!

35:10.858 --> 35:11.938
[yelping]

35:12.610 --> 35:13.610
[groans] [grunts]

35:19.826 --> 35:20.826
Bagheera.

35:21.619 --> 35:22.499
If you will.

35:22.620 --> 35:23.830
[Bagheera roars]

35:24.956 --> 35:26.996
- [wolves barking]
- [Mowgli yelling]

35:32.171 --> 35:33.171
[grunts]

35:38.553 --> 35:40.563
[yells]

35:51.399 --> 35:52.899
- [wolf whines]
- [Mowgli groans]

36:06.247 --> 36:07.957
[wolf] Out of my way, freak!

36:10.626 --> 36:11.876
[panting]

36:16.424 --> 36:18.434
[birds squawking]

36:27.059 --> 36:28.899
- [Bagheera roars]
- [wolves whine]

36:35.276 --> 36:36.736
[Bagheera roars]

36:36.819 --> 36:37.819
[whining]

36:42.241 --> 36:44.911
[Mowgli yelps] Ah!

36:46.370 --> 36:47.410
[snarls]

36:49.123 --> 36:50.713
[Mowgli pants]

36:55.004 --> 36:56.304
- [roars]
- [Mowgli gasps]

37:00.801 --> 37:01.801
[Mowgli grunts]

37:02.386 --> 37:04.926
- [roars]
- [gasps and yells]

37:05.723 --> 37:08.273
- [Mowgli yelling and grunting]
- [roaring]

37:09.143 --> 37:10.353
[Mowgli grunting]

37:16.275 --> 37:18.025
[roars]

37:24.867 --> 37:26.867
[wolves barking and growling]

37:34.043 --> 37:35.043
[grunts]

37:54.230 --> 37:55.980
- [Bagheera roars]
- [Mowgli yelps]

37:59.151 --> 38:00.151
[roars]

38:02.405 --> 38:04.025
[screaming]

38:04.991 --> 38:06.411
[Baloo] Let him go, Bagheera.

38:08.577 --> 38:09.407
Bagheera...

38:09.495 --> 38:10.785
[roars]

38:15.876 --> 38:17.416
[Mowgli pants]

38:24.719 --> 38:26.719
[snorts]

38:32.476 --> 38:33.476
Get up.

38:37.148 --> 38:38.768
[whimpering]

38:54.749 --> 38:56.709
You let your guard down.

38:58.419 --> 39:01.879
I told you, never let your guard down.

39:01.964 --> 39:03.384
He was only chasing <i>me.</i>

39:03.466 --> 39:04.836
He targeted <i> me.</i>

39:04.925 --> 39:06.385
He knows I'm the weakest.

39:07.511 --> 39:09.261
[sighs]

39:11.182 --> 39:13.062
[Mowgli whimpers]

39:13.434 --> 39:14.984
All of your lessons...

39:15.770 --> 39:17.270
[shouts] ...they mean nothing!

39:21.400 --> 39:22.400
[Bagheera] Mowgli!

39:22.485 --> 39:24.145
Bagheera! He's fine.

39:25.029 --> 39:26.029
Let him be.

39:26.447 --> 39:27.777
[wolf] See ya, freak!

39:30.076 --> 39:32.076
[Mowgli pants and grunts]

39:34.747 --> 39:37.827
- [laughs]
- [flies buzzing]

39:38.918 --> 39:40.708
[kite screeches]

39:58.312 --> 39:59.442
[monkey calls]

40:08.614 --> 40:10.324
[monkey chittering]

40:14.829 --> 40:16.709
[Mowgli grunting]

40:23.587 --> 40:24.587
Hey, Mowgli.

40:25.506 --> 40:27.796
[Bhoot chuckling] Oh!

40:32.138 --> 40:33.138
Ha!

40:33.431 --> 40:35.061
- [Mowgli gasps] Ah!
- [Bhoot shrieks]

40:35.474 --> 40:37.354
[Mowgli yelling]

40:39.228 --> 40:41.268
I saw that look in your eye

40:41.355 --> 40:43.105
when you were standing over him.

40:43.190 --> 40:45.730
I did what I did because I had to.

40:45.818 --> 40:47.448
Do you think I am stupid?

40:47.528 --> 40:49.908
[shouts] I saw what you did!

40:49.989 --> 40:51.909
[both roaring]

40:52.032 --> 40:55.662
[Mowgli yelling] Help! Help! Help!

40:55.786 --> 40:57.286
He was in the lead!

40:57.580 --> 40:59.330
I trained that boy!

40:59.415 --> 41:01.245
Why did you have to do that?

41:01.333 --> 41:03.753
- [Bagheera] He had to fail!
- [yells]

41:03.836 --> 41:07.086
[Bagheera]
Why can't you see how much danger he's in?

41:07.173 --> 41:10.013
[Baloo] The pack would have protected him!

41:11.051 --> 41:16.311
Khan will kill him
and tear the pack apart.

41:17.266 --> 41:19.596
You are not the only one

41:19.685 --> 41:21.595
who cares about the boy.

41:21.687 --> 41:24.517
All you care about is that he passed.

41:24.607 --> 41:28.317
That is because it's my job!

41:28.402 --> 41:31.112
[Bhoot whines]
Bagheera! Baloo! Up here!

41:31.197 --> 41:33.237
Mowgli's been taken by the monkey-people!

41:33.324 --> 41:34.704
[both panting]

41:34.783 --> 41:35.873
[kite screeches]

41:37.786 --> 41:39.036
[roars]

41:39.121 --> 41:40.711
- Mowgli!
- Mowgli!

41:40.873 --> 41:42.883
[monkeys screeching] [Mowgli yelling]

42:00.809 --> 42:02.809
[monkeys eeking excitedly]

42:04.813 --> 42:06.073
[Mowgli grunts] Let go!

42:08.484 --> 42:09.494
Let me go!

42:13.614 --> 42:17.624
[Mowgli grunting and screaming]

42:21.997 --> 42:23.037
[Mowgli yelps] Ah!

42:23.123 --> 42:24.123
[thuds]

42:28.837 --> 42:30.417
[flies buzzing]

42:37.555 --> 42:39.555
[monkeys screeching]

42:43.602 --> 42:45.192
[clanging]

42:46.480 --> 42:48.480
[snarling]

42:49.525 --> 42:51.775
[Mowgli huffs and puffs]

43:00.619 --> 43:01.619
[snarling]

43:12.506 --> 43:13.626
[groans]

43:16.885 --> 43:18.795
[kite screeches]

43:18.887 --> 43:21.347
[loud roar]

43:39.908 --> 43:41.908
[Tabaqui laughing]

43:48.292 --> 43:49.882
[monkey screeches]

43:54.256 --> 43:56.256
[growling]

43:59.970 --> 44:02.720
My, my.

44:04.350 --> 44:06.690
How you've grown.

44:08.312 --> 44:09.362
[monkey yelps]

44:10.981 --> 44:14.611
And how much chaos
you brought upon the pack.

44:16.528 --> 44:20.868
So much more...

44:22.201 --> 44:23.581
to come.

44:23.952 --> 44:26.042
[growls]

44:34.171 --> 44:35.171
Just...

44:36.382 --> 44:38.682
a little taste.

44:40.803 --> 44:42.183
[roof cracking]

44:43.847 --> 44:45.347
[Baloo yells, grunts]

44:46.850 --> 44:48.850
[roaring]

44:49.395 --> 44:50.725
[monkeys screeching]

44:51.271 --> 44:52.271
Mowgli!

44:53.816 --> 44:54.816
[snarling]

44:55.442 --> 44:56.692
[roaring]

44:56.819 --> 44:58.819
[monkeys screeching]

45:01.990 --> 45:03.280
[roars]

45:07.496 --> 45:08.616
[Bagheera roars]

45:09.790 --> 45:10.830
[monkey screams]

45:11.166 --> 45:12.326
[both roar]

45:14.294 --> 45:16.304
[monkeys screeching]
[Bagheera gasps and roars]

45:22.636 --> 45:24.636
[growling]

45:24.972 --> 45:26.012
Bagheera!

45:26.432 --> 45:28.232
[Bagheera groans]

45:30.227 --> 45:32.227
[Baloo roars]

45:37.985 --> 45:39.105
[hissing]

45:42.614 --> 45:44.624
[Shere Khan gasps]

45:56.879 --> 46:00.339
Let the man-cub alone.

46:00.799 --> 46:02.049
He belongs...

46:02.342 --> 46:04.182
to us. [hisses]

46:06.722 --> 46:08.022
[growls]

46:15.606 --> 46:17.226
[Mowgli groans]

46:23.822 --> 46:25.822
[monkeys screeching] [birds chittering]

46:33.499 --> 46:35.499
[water flowing]

46:47.429 --> 46:48.429
Kaa...

46:52.226 --> 46:53.806
She saved me.

47:00.776 --> 47:01.776
Why?

47:13.705 --> 47:16.035
[wolves howling]

47:23.841 --> 47:24.971
[Akela] Good hunting!

47:25.634 --> 47:26.974
[wolves] Good hunting all!

47:27.094 --> 47:29.104
[wolves howl and bark]

47:29.930 --> 47:31.010
[Akela] Good hunting!

47:31.223 --> 47:32.643
[wolves] Good hunting all!

47:35.394 --> 47:36.484
[Bhoot] Mowgli!

47:37.271 --> 47:38.271
Hey, Mowgli.

47:38.313 --> 47:40.733
- [cracks]
- [Bhoot gasps and laughs]

47:44.278 --> 47:45.278
Don't worry.

47:45.737 --> 47:47.487
We'll get to join them soon enough.

47:47.739 --> 47:48.909
I just know it.

47:49.241 --> 47:53.701
Mum says, some wolves just need more time.
It doesn't mean we're not good enough.

47:54.079 --> 47:56.579
Hey, why don't we have our own night hunt?

47:56.957 --> 47:59.127
Just you and me.
What do you say?

48:00.878 --> 48:01.878
[Mowgli sighs]

48:03.547 --> 48:05.007
[sighs]

48:05.173 --> 48:08.263
You've been spending a lot of time
on your own since the monkey-people.

48:08.510 --> 48:09.890
It's not good to be alone.

48:09.970 --> 48:11.690
Wolves are supposed to be
with other wolves.

48:11.722 --> 48:12.722
I'm not a wolf.

48:13.765 --> 48:15.925
[laughs]

48:17.519 --> 48:19.349
Of course you are, Mowgli.

48:19.438 --> 48:20.898
You're the best wolf I know!

48:21.607 --> 48:23.977
Why do you always want to be
around me, Bhoot?

48:24.359 --> 48:26.239
'Cause you're my best friend, Mowgli.

48:29.698 --> 48:31.158
[Mowgli sighs]

48:34.077 --> 48:35.077
[snorts]

48:36.038 --> 48:37.498
I understand what it's like.

48:39.082 --> 48:40.252
For nobody to want you.

48:44.463 --> 48:46.173
I don't have any friends neither.

48:47.382 --> 48:48.222
But...

48:48.300 --> 48:49.340
we have each other.

48:50.052 --> 48:51.852
And we're kind of same, you and me.

48:51.929 --> 48:53.059
We're not the same.

48:53.138 --> 48:54.308
Of course we are.

48:54.389 --> 48:56.559
Because you're special and I'm special.

48:56.642 --> 48:58.482
[shouts] We're not special!

48:59.227 --> 49:00.307
Don't you get it?

49:01.063 --> 49:03.573
We'll never be one of them!
We're freaks!

49:04.274 --> 49:06.494
You're not special, Bhoot!

49:07.110 --> 49:10.860
It's just something your mother tells you
to make you feel better about yourself...

49:10.948 --> 49:13.488
because you came out wrong!

49:15.035 --> 49:17.035
[whimpers]

49:31.426 --> 49:32.426
Bhoot...

49:33.679 --> 49:34.849
Bhoot, I'm sorry.

50:04.710 --> 50:06.710
[leaves rustling]

50:29.401 --> 50:30.861
[Akela yells]

50:32.237 --> 50:33.527
[wolves panting]

50:38.994 --> 50:39.994
Kaa?

50:44.916 --> 50:45.916
Kaa.

50:46.710 --> 50:48.000
Well,

50:48.754 --> 50:50.634
look who's here.

50:52.716 --> 50:54.086
It's the man-cub,

50:54.593 --> 50:58.063
his destiny still uncertain.

50:59.264 --> 51:02.314
Are you afraid of me, man-cub?

51:04.311 --> 51:05.311
No.

51:07.022 --> 51:09.072
Sometimes fear...

51:09.983 --> 51:12.743
is the only intelligent response.

51:16.364 --> 51:17.364
Don't you think?

51:17.449 --> 51:19.449
[breathes shakily]

51:23.872 --> 51:25.712
Say something...

51:28.710 --> 51:30.460
or I shall get bored.

51:33.673 --> 51:35.883
And when I get bored...

51:37.052 --> 51:38.642
I get hungry.

51:41.056 --> 51:42.056
Is it...

51:43.100 --> 51:46.850
Is it true that you know the past
and the future?

51:47.521 --> 51:50.071
What is it you want from me...

51:50.732 --> 51:51.572
man-cub?

51:51.650 --> 51:54.030
Why did you save me
from the monkey-people?

51:54.778 --> 51:58.818
Why do you think
the elephant saved you from the tiger pit?

52:00.200 --> 52:05.040
The whole jungle has been watching you,
man-cub.

52:06.414 --> 52:07.414
Why?

52:07.874 --> 52:11.554
Even you must know you are unusual.

52:14.214 --> 52:16.094
Not quite a wolf,

52:16.174 --> 52:17.594
not quite a man...

52:18.468 --> 52:19.468
or neither...

52:20.095 --> 52:21.095
or both.

52:21.930 --> 52:23.270
[Mowgli gasps]

52:23.348 --> 52:25.348
[grunts]

52:30.438 --> 52:31.938
[wolves panting]

52:32.023 --> 52:34.033
[Akela roars]

52:41.283 --> 52:44.163
I think we can both agree, Mowgli,

52:44.244 --> 52:49.174
that you are something
the jungle has never seen before.

52:49.249 --> 52:51.249
[wolves howl]

52:52.669 --> 52:53.999
[Akela sighs]

52:54.671 --> 52:56.761
Every day...

52:57.465 --> 53:00.335
you grow a little older.

53:01.219 --> 53:02.469
Every day...

53:03.388 --> 53:06.308
you come a little closer.

53:08.101 --> 53:10.731
- One day you will fight...
- [distant screams echoing]

53:10.896 --> 53:12.016
...and kill.

53:14.983 --> 53:17.283
One day you will speak...

53:18.278 --> 53:21.108
and the jungle will listen.

53:26.953 --> 53:31.043
[distorted]
What will you say then, man-cub?

53:35.295 --> 53:36.295
Do you hear?

53:36.755 --> 53:38.755
[wolves howling] The entertainment...

53:43.470 --> 53:45.220
commences.

53:47.349 --> 53:49.389
I shall be watching.

53:50.769 --> 53:52.769
- [monkeys screeching]
- [wolves howling]

53:55.065 --> 53:57.605
You have no right to be here, Shere Khan!

53:58.526 --> 54:02.986
Well, I think you'll find
I stay where I please.

54:03.073 --> 54:04.823
[Tabaqui laughs]

54:06.034 --> 54:09.044
You kill man's cattle.
You poison the jungle.

54:09.621 --> 54:11.291
You're the reason man is here!

54:11.373 --> 54:14.583
But <i>you</i> permitted man to live among you.

54:14.876 --> 54:17.796
<i>You</i> pretend he is a wolf.

54:18.255 --> 54:21.085
When we both know
that is the one thing he will never be.

54:21.841 --> 54:24.391
He will always be...

54:24.636 --> 54:26.176
a man.

54:27.013 --> 54:28.013
<i>You...</i>

54:28.556 --> 54:30.806
poisoned the jungle.

54:32.477 --> 54:35.557
But you're no longer leader now,

54:35.647 --> 54:36.647
are you?

54:37.190 --> 54:38.650
You missed your kill.

54:38.733 --> 54:40.743
[Tabaqui laughs]

54:42.445 --> 54:43.985
By your law...

54:45.740 --> 54:46.780
your pack...

54:48.034 --> 54:49.334
must challenge you.

54:49.411 --> 54:51.291
[Tabaqui laughs]

54:51.371 --> 54:56.001
Akela's missed his kill!
Akela's missed his kill!

54:56.084 --> 54:57.754
- [laughing]
- [monkeys screeching]

55:00.839 --> 55:04.089
[Akela] As is our tradition,
whoever defeats me...

55:05.010 --> 55:06.760
will become leader of the pack.

55:07.679 --> 55:09.679
[wolves snarling] [growling and thudding]

55:15.520 --> 55:17.110
[wolf whines]

55:18.940 --> 55:20.480
[wolves snarling]

55:20.984 --> 55:21.864
What's happening?

55:21.943 --> 55:24.203
[growling and whining]

55:24.279 --> 55:25.569
[grunting]

55:26.031 --> 55:26.911
Mowgli!

55:26.990 --> 55:28.160
It's the law.

55:28.325 --> 55:30.325
[wolves growling] -[growls]
- [whining]

55:39.002 --> 55:39.922
Who's next?

55:40.003 --> 55:42.013
[wolves growl]

55:43.631 --> 55:44.921
[Akela yelps]

55:47.469 --> 55:49.469
- [monkeys screeching]
- [wolves howling]

56:08.073 --> 56:09.743
[howls]

56:10.533 --> 56:11.533
[Mowgli gasps]

56:25.090 --> 56:26.510
- [yelling]
- [gasps]

56:38.061 --> 56:40.061
[panting]

56:45.110 --> 56:45.940
Who's next?

56:46.027 --> 56:47.027
No!

56:47.112 --> 56:48.322
Mowgli!

56:48.655 --> 56:50.985
[wolves bark and whine]

56:51.116 --> 56:52.486
[Shere Khan roars]

56:56.287 --> 56:57.287
No!

56:59.707 --> 57:02.587
[Mowgli grunting]

57:09.300 --> 57:10.970
- [fire whooshes]
- [Shere Khan roars]

57:11.052 --> 57:16.812
If I ever see you here again,
I will set your hide ablaze

57:16.891 --> 57:19.231
and watch you burn alive!

57:19.310 --> 57:22.940
[roars] I will taste your blood,

57:23.356 --> 57:24.896
man-cub.

57:25.650 --> 57:27.320
[wolves whimpering]

57:27.402 --> 57:29.242
[fire crackling]

57:36.411 --> 57:37.411
Leave.

57:37.537 --> 57:39.537
[Akela and Mowgli panting]

57:43.126 --> 57:44.126
What?

57:44.961 --> 57:45.961
You have...

57:47.005 --> 57:49.005
turned the weapons of man...

57:50.049 --> 57:51.129
upon us.

57:53.136 --> 57:55.926
You have brought the pack great shame.

57:56.431 --> 57:57.851
You have brought me...

57:59.434 --> 58:00.524
great shame.

58:02.937 --> 58:03.937
Leave.

58:04.606 --> 58:06.606
[wolves whining]
[thunder crashes and rumbles]

58:55.156 --> 58:57.156
[thunder crashes] [indistinct chattering]

59:10.755 --> 59:12.755
[Mowgli grunts]

59:22.559 --> 59:23.559
[thuds]

59:51.004 --> 59:52.924
[birds tweeting]

59:59.887 --> 01:00:01.887
[distant voices chattering]
[planks creaking]

01:00:09.981 --> 01:00:11.481
- [banging]
- [Mowgli grunts]

01:00:16.654 --> 01:00:18.664
[cows mooing] [people chattering]

01:00:34.255 --> 01:00:36.255
- [cow moos]
- [bell dings]

01:00:44.474 --> 01:00:47.104
- [footsteps]
- [planks creak]

01:00:53.399 --> 01:00:56.779
[classical music playing over speaker]

01:01:05.286 --> 01:01:08.206
[grunting, yelling]

01:01:23.638 --> 01:01:25.468
[cage clinks open]

01:01:32.563 --> 01:01:34.573
[cage grinds]

01:01:39.946 --> 01:01:41.656
[birds cawing and chirping]

01:01:56.337 --> 01:01:57.957
[sniffs]

01:02:03.803 --> 01:02:04.973
[plate clanks]

01:02:06.556 --> 01:02:07.926
[spitting]

01:02:08.099 --> 01:02:10.099
[people speaking Hindi]

01:02:17.316 --> 01:02:18.316
[Mowgli gasps]

01:02:25.074 --> 01:02:26.704
[children chuckle]

01:02:28.327 --> 01:02:30.457
[laughing]

01:02:37.879 --> 01:02:39.509
- [thumps]
- [Mowgli snarling]

01:02:39.630 --> 01:02:41.090
[yelling]

01:02:55.730 --> 01:02:57.730
- [soft snarling]
- [footsteps approaching]

01:03:09.869 --> 01:03:10.869
- Bagh...
- Shh!

01:03:14.040 --> 01:03:15.040
[Bagheera sighs]

01:03:16.501 --> 01:03:17.501
[chuckles]

01:03:19.879 --> 01:03:21.259
Hello, little brother.

01:03:24.509 --> 01:03:26.509
[quavering] I knew you'd come.

01:03:28.346 --> 01:03:30.636
I knew you'd rescue me.

01:03:31.015 --> 01:03:32.305
[sighs]

01:03:33.559 --> 01:03:34.559
Mowgli...

01:03:38.272 --> 01:03:39.982
I have not come to rescue you.

01:03:41.692 --> 01:03:43.492
I've come to tell you to stay.

01:03:45.905 --> 01:03:46.905
What?

01:03:48.282 --> 01:03:50.282
- [footsteps]
- [planks creak]

01:03:55.373 --> 01:03:58.963
You must stay in the village.
You must not come back to the jungle.

01:03:59.043 --> 01:04:02.513
- But the jungle is my home.
- No, it isn't. Not anymore.

01:04:02.588 --> 01:04:04.378
I can't stay here.
- Yes, you can. I can't.

01:04:07.760 --> 01:04:10.100
You will learn to understand their ways.

01:04:10.179 --> 01:04:11.259
You may even grow...

01:04:11.347 --> 01:04:13.467
[takes a deep breath] ...to like it.

01:04:15.017 --> 01:04:16.057
It'll be all right,

01:04:16.644 --> 01:04:17.564
little brother.

01:04:17.645 --> 01:04:20.855
How do you know? You've never spent a day
outside the jungle.

01:04:20.940 --> 01:04:22.020
[gasps]

01:04:22.316 --> 01:04:24.316
[Bagheera purrs]

01:04:28.364 --> 01:04:29.954
I was born among man.

01:04:31.993 --> 01:04:34.003
[Bagheera sighs]

01:04:35.329 --> 01:04:37.619
I bear the marks of a collar.

01:04:39.125 --> 01:04:40.245
Under my chin.

01:04:44.755 --> 01:04:47.625
I lived in a king's palace
in a cage just like this.

01:04:48.593 --> 01:04:49.763
Fed through a slot.

01:04:51.637 --> 01:04:53.057
Man's entertainment.

01:04:55.933 --> 01:04:58.943
I only heard stories about the jungle.

01:05:02.398 --> 01:05:03.478
When I found you...

01:05:04.901 --> 01:05:06.241
all those seasons ago...

01:05:08.529 --> 01:05:10.699
[sighs] ...I saw something in you.

01:05:12.491 --> 01:05:15.831
And I thought I could teach you.
I thought I could...

01:05:16.162 --> 01:05:18.162
[takes a deep breath]

01:05:18.706 --> 01:05:20.206
...teach you how to belong.

01:05:21.208 --> 01:05:23.338
To be like everyone else.

01:05:26.881 --> 01:05:28.511
But I was wrong, Mowgli.

01:05:29.133 --> 01:05:30.803
You weren't wrong. [sobs]

01:05:35.097 --> 01:05:36.097
I was wrong.

01:05:38.893 --> 01:05:40.193
Bagheera...

01:05:42.104 --> 01:05:43.564
I love you.

01:05:55.826 --> 01:05:57.666
I was another panther...
in that cage, Mowgli.

01:06:00.581 --> 01:06:01.581
I bit...

01:06:02.375 --> 01:06:03.785
and I scratched...

01:06:05.086 --> 01:06:08.046
and I spent my entire life fighting.

01:06:10.091 --> 01:06:11.091
Until one day...

01:06:12.468 --> 01:06:13.588
I just stopped.

01:06:15.888 --> 01:06:16.888
[sighs]

01:06:17.974 --> 01:06:19.144
I stopped fighting.

01:06:22.353 --> 01:06:23.603
And I gained their trust.

01:06:25.189 --> 01:06:27.069
Gain their trust, little brother.

01:06:36.117 --> 01:06:37.577
Bagheera...

01:06:38.411 --> 01:06:41.041
Don't leave me here.

01:06:43.833 --> 01:06:45.843
[shouting] Come back!

01:07:21.370 --> 01:07:22.460
[birds tweeting]

01:07:22.913 --> 01:07:24.923
[men chattering] [cows mooing]

01:07:45.144 --> 01:07:47.154
[knife sharpening] [cow bells jingling]

01:08:05.289 --> 01:08:06.289
Hey!

01:08:12.505 --> 01:08:13.505
[sighs]

01:08:36.194 --> 01:08:37.354
[imitates slicing] Shh-ha.

01:08:41.117 --> 01:08:42.117
Shh-ha.

01:08:43.661 --> 01:08:44.791
Shh-ha.

01:08:48.124 --> 01:08:49.674
[slicing]

01:08:55.798 --> 01:08:57.008
You're a fast learner.

01:08:59.760 --> 01:09:00.890
[speaking Hindi]

01:09:02.138 --> 01:09:03.428
[in English] Prefer mine cooked.

01:09:05.265 --> 01:09:06.265
[sighs]

01:09:11.354 --> 01:09:12.895
I, uh, noticed your scar.

01:09:21.823 --> 01:09:22.823
Tiger.

01:09:26.578 --> 01:09:28.709
Looks like we've both got the same enemy.

01:09:43.720 --> 01:09:45.140
[birds tweeting]

01:10:04.116 --> 01:10:05.196
[Mowgli gasps]

01:10:05.284 --> 01:10:06.834
[speaking Hindi]

01:10:07.119 --> 01:10:09.289
It's nothing to worry about.

01:10:10.122 --> 01:10:11.122
Hmm?

01:10:12.166 --> 01:10:13.666
It's all right, it's nothing.

01:10:28.724 --> 01:10:30.734
[singing in Hindi]

01:10:51.914 --> 01:10:54.214
Here, you can keep this one.

01:10:54.291 --> 01:10:55.291
Hmm?

01:10:57.211 --> 01:10:59.211
[Messua continues singing in Hindi]

01:11:22.361 --> 01:11:24.201
[people speaking Hindi]

01:11:37.626 --> 01:11:39.626
- [boy yelling]
- [cows mooing]

01:11:50.222 --> 01:11:51.222
[boy gasps]

01:11:57.813 --> 01:11:58.943
[chuckles]

01:12:12.661 --> 01:12:14.161
[dogs barking]

01:12:19.626 --> 01:12:20.626
Oh! [chuckles]

01:12:30.679 --> 01:12:32.679
[children shouting]

01:12:35.559 --> 01:12:37.439
[speaking Hindi]

01:12:44.568 --> 01:12:46.358
- [all laughing]
- [cow moos]

01:12:52.117 --> 01:12:54.327
[Lockwood in English]
It's so you can hunt.

01:13:01.251 --> 01:13:02.251
There.

01:13:21.105 --> 01:13:23.725
- [children playing]
- [people speaking Hindi]

01:13:28.070 --> 01:13:30.070
[kite screeches]
[children chattering and laughing]

01:13:40.707 --> 01:13:41.997
[kite screeches]

01:13:44.002 --> 01:13:46.592
[chirping]

01:13:56.723 --> 01:13:57.723
Hello, brother!

01:13:59.601 --> 01:14:01.281
[pants] Hello, Mowgli. You look different.

01:14:14.575 --> 01:14:15.615
Why are you here?

01:14:16.118 --> 01:14:17.238
It's Shere Khan.

01:14:18.203 --> 01:14:19.293
He's taken over.

01:14:20.205 --> 01:14:21.615
We've had to leave home.

01:14:21.707 --> 01:14:23.827
Those of us
who still stand by Akela, anyway.

01:14:23.917 --> 01:14:25.997
And... the others?

01:14:26.295 --> 01:14:28.455
They come in groups, in the night.

01:14:29.840 --> 01:14:30.840
Threaten us.

01:14:31.842 --> 01:14:32.972
Our own people.

01:14:35.679 --> 01:14:37.309
It's not my problem anymore.

01:14:37.389 --> 01:14:39.349
- Mowgli...
- It's not my problem.

01:14:39.433 --> 01:14:41.853
We've been pushed to the very edge
of the jungle.

01:14:42.811 --> 01:14:44.981
And Khan won't stop killing man's cattle.

01:14:45.397 --> 01:14:46.397
Brother...

01:14:48.108 --> 01:14:50.148
We're afraid of what man might do to us.

01:14:54.072 --> 01:14:55.822
The pack needs you, Mowgli.

01:14:57.910 --> 01:15:00.000
They didn't need me when I was cast out.

01:15:06.710 --> 01:15:07.710
Please! Come home.

01:15:20.974 --> 01:15:22.314
This is my home now.

01:15:23.519 --> 01:15:25.099
[musical instrument drumming]

01:15:25.187 --> 01:15:27.187
[people laughing, chattering]

01:15:36.031 --> 01:15:38.121
[Hindi music playing]

01:15:55.092 --> 01:15:56.642
[boy speaking Hindi]

01:16:37.301 --> 01:16:38.971
[laughing]

01:17:00.657 --> 01:17:01.657
[man speaking Hindi]

01:17:01.742 --> 01:17:02.782
Lockwood,

01:17:04.536 --> 01:17:08.616
when will you kill the tiger?
He has killed many cattle.

01:17:09.249 --> 01:17:10.379
[in English] A clever beast.

01:17:12.836 --> 01:17:14.416
Knows how to cover his tracks.

01:17:16.798 --> 01:17:20.298
[in Hindi]
Have you ever missed?

01:17:21.261 --> 01:17:22.351
Just once,

01:17:23.513 --> 01:17:24.513
just once.

01:17:27.017 --> 01:17:29.017
Tiger?

01:17:31.647 --> 01:17:32.687
[in English] Elephant.

01:17:37.027 --> 01:17:39.277
I did get one of his tusks, though.

01:17:40.739 --> 01:17:43.329
[in Hindi]
I have never missed a kill since.

01:17:44.409 --> 01:17:45.789
[fire crackling]

01:17:52.834 --> 01:17:55.424
I will get your tiger.

01:17:59.257 --> 01:18:01.467
[in English]
I have no doubt, I will get him.

01:18:05.347 --> 01:18:06.347
I will get him.

01:18:08.308 --> 01:18:09.518
[bottle shatters]

01:18:20.987 --> 01:18:22.737
[classical music playing from speaker]

01:18:27.244 --> 01:18:28.374
[groans]

01:18:57.524 --> 01:18:59.154
[music stops]

01:19:00.819 --> 01:19:02.819
[planks creaking]

01:19:56.333 --> 01:19:57.333
[gasps]

01:20:04.466 --> 01:20:05.716
[in English] Beautiful...

01:20:06.802 --> 01:20:07.802
isn't he?

01:20:12.182 --> 01:20:13.812
My first albino.

01:20:18.396 --> 01:20:19.436
And this...

01:20:19.981 --> 01:20:22.981
is my own personal menagerie.

01:20:29.783 --> 01:20:32.623
You don't understand...

01:20:33.787 --> 01:20:35.997
a word I'm saying,

01:20:36.081 --> 01:20:37.081
do you?

01:20:43.713 --> 01:20:45.673
We can't all be scholars.

01:20:49.594 --> 01:20:51.604
Because God knows I'm not.

01:21:01.898 --> 01:21:03.318
[sobbing softly]

01:21:14.786 --> 01:21:16.786
[birds chittering]

